The paper deals with list decoding of error-correcting codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm presented in the paper is based on multivariate polynomial interpolation and root-finding, which are techniques commonly used in computational complexity (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves linear algebraic techniques, which are relevant to both computer science theory (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI). Overall, the paper could potentially fit into any of these sub-categories, but cs.IT and cs.DS seem to be the most likely based on the content of the abstract.
